'''''Star Wars'' 8''' is the eighth issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Roy Thomas]] and [[Howard Chaykin]], with art by Chaykin and [[Tom Palmer]], and it was first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[November 8]], [[1977]]. It features the story "'''Eight for Aduba-3'''," which introduces [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] to an array of new characters, including [[Jaxxon/Legends|Jaxxon]], [[Amaiza Foxtrain/Legends|Amaiza Foxtrain]], and the [[Cloud-Riders/Legends|Cloud-Riders]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Han and Chewie take a new job defending a moisture farmer from a local gang known as the Cloud-Riders.''

==Plot summary==
Han Solo and Chewbacca are hired by [[Ramiz]], a moisture farmer on [[Aduba-3/Legends|Aduba-3]], to protect his village from a band of local thugs known as the Cloud-Riders, led by [[Serji-X Arrogantus]]. Han and Chewbacca hire six misfit [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]] to help them with the task, including [[Don-Wan Kihotay]], an old man who thinks he is a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]], and [[Jaxxon/Legends|Jaxxon]], a [[Rabbit/Legends|rabbit]]-like [[Lepi/Legends|Lepi]] with a mean disposition. Serji-X tries to convince Han to forget about his mission to protect the peasants and even offers him compensation, but Han declines.

Meanwhile, on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] leave in a [[Luke Skywalker's scout ship|scout ship]] to search for a location for the new [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] base.

